&lt;p&gt;â€œéšâ€ å±•ç°ä½œè€…çš„å€’å½±&lt;br /&gt;
æ–‡å­¦å®¶å†™ä¹¦ï¼Œå¤šå¤šå°‘å°‘éƒ½ä¼šåœ¨ä¹¦ä¸­å½±å°„è‡ªå·±ã€‚è€Œåœ¨ã€Šçº¢æ¥¼æ¢¦ã€‹ä¸­ï¼Œæ•´éƒ¨ä¹¦éƒ½æ˜¯åœ¨ â€œçœŸäº‹éšâ€ çš„å‰æä¸‹å±•å¼€çš„ï¼Œâ€œçœŸäº‹â€ æŒ‡çš„ä»€ä¹ˆè‡ªç„¶ä¸è¨€è€Œå–» â€”â€” æ˜¯æ›¹é›ªèŠ¹å®¶é“ä¸­è½å‰çš„ç”Ÿæ´»ã€‚èº«ä¸ºæ±Ÿå—ç»‡é€ ä¹‹å®¶çš„å…¬å­ï¼Œä»–åœ¨æ±Ÿå—äº«å—äº†è£åå¯Œè´µï¼Œç”šè‡³ä¹¾éš†çš‡å¸å—å·¡éƒ½åœ¨ä»–ä»¬åºœä¸­è½è„šã€‚ä»ä¸€æ–¹é¢æ¥è¯´ï¼Œè¿™äº›ä¸Šæµç¤¾ä¼šçš„ç”Ÿæ´»æ—¶æ›¹é›ªèŠ¹æ¥è§¦äº†å¤§é‡çš„çŸ¥è¯†ï¼Œä»–å‡ºç¥å…¥åŒ–çš„æœé¥°æå†™å°±å¯ä»¥è¯æ˜ã€‚å¦ä¸€æ–¹é¢ï¼Œä»–ä¹Ÿè§è¯†äº†ä¸Šæµç¤¾ä¼šçš„è…æœ½ï¼Œåœ¨è¢«æŠ„å®¶åä»–äºæ˜¯åæ€è¿™ä¸€åˆ‡çš„å¼€ç«¯ï¼Œäºæ˜¯å°±æœ‰äº†è­¦é†’ä¸–äººçš„ã€Šçº¢æ¥¼æ¢¦ã€‹ã€‚ä»æŸç§ç¨‹åº¦ä¸Šè¯´ï¼Œã€Šçº¢æ¥¼æ¢¦ã€‹ä¸­è´¾åºœæ­£æ˜¯æ›¹åºœã€‚&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;æ€»ä¹‹&lt;br /&gt;
 â€œéšâ€ æˆå°±äº†ã€Šçº¢æ¥¼æ¢¦ã€‹ï¼Œä¸ºè¯»è€…å±•å¼€äº†ä¸€ä¸ªä¸ä¹¦å¹³è¡Œçš„ä¸–ç•Œï¼Œä½¿æ›¹é›ªèŠ¹è‡ªå·±çš„å€’å½±è¡æ¼¾åœ¨è¯»è€…çš„è„‘æµ·ä¸­ã€‚&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;comments-on-fence-or-ambulance&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#comments-on-fence-or-ambulance&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Comments on &amp;quot;Fence or ambulance&amp;quot;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Despite the fact that this classical poem was written approximately 130 years ago, the discussion of whether construct a fence or assemble a fleet of ambulances down in that hypothetical valley continued to this day. As a part of the content itself, peopleâ€™s opinions towards the two options were mentioned: some of them were advocates of the ambulance, as it seemed straightforward enough to those people; some, however, believed the fence is better as it prevented any further tragedies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In my point of view, same with the author, a fence is certainly better than an ambulance. It can be explained through multiple aspects, and Iâ€™m in favor of these two: cost and effect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In terms of cost, the fence is certainly a lot cheaper in different ways. Though ambulances are indeed flexible, it is widely acknowledged that operating them requires a fortune: not just the cost of vehicles, but also expenses of medical instruments as well as labor cost should be added. For the fence, it only requires the initial installation cost and regular maintenance. Nevertheless, both plans are capable of saving lives, yet at different costs, and it is apparent to judge which is more economic. In our school lives, time is what matters the most, and time cost of different learning styles is visible. Going through different subjects altogether at the end of the month require several days and even a whole week, yet completing revision tasks daily only takes minutes. Iâ€™m uncertain about othersâ€™ choices, but Iâ€™m going to build my â€œfenceâ€ day by day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Referring to effect, the fence reaches a far more realistic outcome. Ambulances evidently rescue people that are already in danger, and dying in some cases might be inevitable, as it takes time for the ambulance to arrive, which means they cannot save all lives or have a better result. On the other hand, fences prevent people from standing close to the cliff, thus nobody would fall. Surly the fence can save all lives quickly and with no further matters to worry. Similar in our lives, stopping the cause of problems is a lot convenient than repairing consequences. It is always a better option to improve our studies by going through textbooks and mistakes daily than do a lot of exercises after countless mistakes. The first way can stop most problems in the future, yet the latter only tackles with the current situation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To sum up, the fence option is more appealing than ambulances, as it can reach a better outcome with relatively little effort. Having said that, it is still uneasy to build a fence of your own, owing to the fact that fences require the persistence of yourself. Nevertheless, fences stand out.&lt;/p&gt;
